column5: Hi all, I'm gonna bombard you with videos this month, lol, have just got around to editing all the ones from this summer, hope that's ok. Went out to lac Seul last week with bass on my mind, they school up on top of a reef i know and provide non stop action slip bobbers and jigs as usual, worms and minnows, all around 10' to 18' FOW.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r2LQT9ANr6I
love that boat. Is it new this year? Great fishing set up. I hear the road to Lac Seul can be nasty. Looks to be the right size to make the trip. Very nice fishing set up. Keep them coming.
